<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Ambassador</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">German
                                        Embassy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-02-28"><hi rend="italic">February 28,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum.</hi></p>
                        <p>Owing to recent menaces of German interests in China it appears probable
                            that the last German warship, now in the Philippines, will be recalled
                            from there. In this case the German Government has expressed the hope
                            that the protection of life and property of German citizens, and of such
                            people enjoying German protection in the Philippines, will be undertaken
                            by the United States forces.</p>
                    </div>
